<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>They launched Operation Fiela Reclaim II at the Embalenhle Sasol Club in Secunda.Immediately after the event, the police at Kaapmuiden, while busy doing their rounds, arrested the 38 year-old man found in possession of two sets of Rhino horns, at the Nkomazi Plaza.The cops stopped a sedan which was driven by the man during a stop-and-search.They then noticed that the man had a cooler box placed on the passenger seat and upon opening it, they made the discovery.The Provincial Commissioner applauded the officers for their alertness that led to the recovery of the horns. He mentioned that poaching of endangered and protected species is one of the problematic crimes in the province and is therefore a priority.The suspect is expected to appear before the Baberton Magistrate's Court on Monday, 05 February 2018.